// DocBrain golden set — retrieval ground truth.
//
// SCHEMA
//   id                : stable identifier, never reuse
//   question          : the question as a real user would phrase it
//   relevant_sources  : list of source-path SUBSTRINGS that correctly answer it.
//                       A list, not a single value — several docs can legitimately be
//                       correct (memory is documented across three separate files), and
//                       demanding one exact file would be a mislabel, not a miss.
//   coverage          : "covered" = the corpus can answer this
//                       "gap"     = the corpus CANNOT answer this (verified by grep).
//                                   Excluded from recall/MRR — scoring these as 0 would
//                                   blame the retriever for a hole in the DATA. Used
//                                   instead to calibrate the "go search the web" threshold.
//   reviewed          : false = labelled by Claude from the file listing, NOT yet checked
//                       by a human. Flip to true once you've confirmed the label.
//
// ⚠️  Every entry below is reviewed=false. These labels are a starting point, not
//     ground truth. A golden set nobody has checked is just a confident-looking guess —
//     go through them, fix the wrong ones, add alternates I missed, then flip the flag.
//
// ── COVERED ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
